Hi folks. I bumped my neovim nightly (trying to stay on the bleeding edge to help the team out as much as possible 🙏🏻 ) today and had the same issue. I also run Nix. Came straight to GitHub to see if I can suggest a config option to change where the lockfile is read from (pretty much what @echasnovski has been advocating for [above](https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/36078#issuecomment-3380258471)). 

A super quick word on Nix though. Maybe this is a skill issue on my side, but I find having two package managers cumbersome. I've done the extremely cursed thing of opting to manage neovim _outside of my Nix store_. There are lots of reasons why this is a good idea but all tangential to the problem.

I found that if I don't move my configuration files in the Nix store and instead symlink I can bypass this issue completely (and I don't have to rebuild my stack for neovim changes as a bonus). See:

```nix
{
  config,
  pkgs,
  lib,
  ...
}: let
  cfg = config.programs.neovim;
  localPath = "${config.home.homeDirectory}/workspace/dotfiles/nvim";
in {
    xdg.configFile."nvim".source = config.lib.file.mkOutOfStoreSymlink localPath;
  };
}
```
[Reference code if you're interested](https://github.com/mateiidavid/dotfiles/blob/main/pkgs/nvim.nix).

For OP (@phenax), if you want to be unblocked, this should do the trick. Sorry if this goes off-topic. Happy to help test and contribute whatever I can here, btw :) 

Thanks all for making the project great!
